or\":\"black\",\"width\":2,\"dash\":\"dot\"},\"name\":\"h(t) — with bouncing event\"}],\"layout\":{\"title\":{\"text\":\"Bouncing ball — with `when h <= 0 and v < 0 then reinit(v, -e*v)`\"},\"showlegend\":true,\"width\":700,\"height\":450,\"plot_bgcolor\":\"white\",\"paper_bgcolor\":\"white\",\"xaxis\":{\"title\":{\"text\":\"t (s)\"},\"showgrid\":true,\"gridcolor\":\"#ddd\",\"linecolor\":\"#ddd\",\"linewidth\":1,\"zerolinecolor\":\"black\",\"zerolinewidth\":1},\"yaxis\":{\"title\":{\"text\":\"h (m)\"},\"showgrid\":true,\"gridcolor\":\"#ddd\",\"linecolor\":\"#ddd\",\"linewidth\":1,\"zerolinecolor\":\"black\",\"zerolinewidth\":1}}}"
            ]
          },
          "metadata": {},
          "output_type": "display_data"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": "Each cusp is a bounce: the ball decelerates as it falls, reverses direction at the floor (with $80\\%$ of its incoming speed because $e = 0.8$), rises to a lower peak, and comes back down. The bounces become arbitrarily close in time — Zeno-like behaviour — but `mod_simulate_nonlinear` has a watchdog (max 100 events per segment) that breaks the loop before it explodes numerically.",
      "metadata": {}
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": "## 5. Phase portrait\n\nPlotting velocity vs height makes the bounces unmistakable: each bounce is a **vertical jump** in the $v$ direction at the $h = 0$ axis (continuous dynamics → smooth curve, discrete reset → straight vertical edge).",
      "metadata": {}
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": "ax_draw2d(\n  color=\"red\", line_width=2, name=\"trajectory\",\n  lines(map(first, x_evt), map(second, x_evt)),\n  marker_size=10, color=\"green\", name=\"start (h=10, v=0)\",\n  points([first(x_evt)[1]], [first(x_evt)[2]]),\n  color=\"black\", dash=\"dot\", name=\"floor\",\n  explicit(v, v, -15, 15),\n  title=\"Bouncing ball phase portrait — h vs v\",\n  xlabel=\"h (m)\", ylabel=\"v (m/s)\",\n  xrange=[-1, 11], yrange=[-15, 15],\n  grid=true, showlegend=true\n)$",
      "metadata": {},
      "execution_count": 24,
      "outputs": [
        {
